 Nigeria’s borrowing plans show the country will look to foreign sources to get about 849 billion naira to fund the 2018 budget deficit. With the US Fed indicating that there are two more rate hikes to come this year, how will international investors respond to Nigeria’s debt drive? CNBC Africa put that question to Gbite Oduneye, founder and CEO of A & O acquisitions. https://www.cnbcafrica.com/videos/